      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Generate exactly 5 test cases for this Jira issue:\n\nIssue: {{ $json.key }} - {{ $json.fields.summary }}\nDescription: {{ $json.fields.description }}\nType: {{ $json.fields.issuetype.name }}\nPriority: {{ $json.fields.priority.name }}\n\nCreate 5 test cases covering:\n1. Happy path scenario\n2. Invalid input scenario\n3. Edge case\n4. Boundary condition\n5. UI validation\n\nReturn a JSON object with a testCases array. Each test case must have:\n- id: Unique identifier (TC001, TC002, etc.)\n- title: Clear test case name\n- preconditions: What must be true before testing\n- steps: Numbered test steps (use actual newlines)\n- expectedResult: What should happen\n- priority: High, Medium, or Low\n- type: Functional, UI, Negative, etc.",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are a QA expert. Always return valid JSON matching the exact schema provided. Each test case must include all required fields: id, title, preconditions, steps, expectedResult, priority, and type.",
          "maxIterations": 10
        }
